    <p>Mozart & Stravin­sky: Mu­sic On The Air</p>
    <p>In this on­line con­cert, the Sin­ga­pore Sym­phony Orches­tra plays pieces in neo-clas­si­cal tra­di­tion. Be in­spired by the muses of Apollo and en­joy a Mozartian ser­e­nade. The per­for­mance was recorded at the Es­planade Con­cert Hall with no au­di­ence last month.</p>
    <p>Sis­tic Live Stream</p>
    <p>To­mor­row, 8pm. The con­cert can be viewed till Sept 12, 8pm.</p>
    <p>Pay as you wish:</p>
    <p>$10, $20, $30 or $50.</p>
    <p>www.sso.org.sg/ orches­tra-sea­son/</p>
    <p>–</p>
    <p>SCO Dig­i­tal Cham­ber Con­cert – Ren­dezvous</p>
    <p>In this on­line con­cert, the Sin­ga­pore Chi­nese Orches­tra will per­form cham­ber mu­sic of con­trast­ing gen­res and cul­tures. It will also fea­ture cham­ber and en­sem­ble works from world-renowned com­posers Chen Qi­gang and Tan</p>
    <p>Dun. Sis­tic Live Stream</p>
    <p>Today, 8pm. The con­cert can be viewed till Sept 6, 10pm.</p>
    <p>$15 www.sis­tic.com.sg/events/</p>
    <p>#DabaoSCO: Ruan Lingyu’s The God­dess – A Silent Film Con­cert</p>
    <p>This on­line con­cert show­cases Chi­nese silent film ac­tress Ruan Lingyu’s re­al­is­tic por­trayal of a mother, ac­com­pa­nied with mu­sic per­formed by the Sin­ga­pore Chi­nese Orches­tra (SCO). The con­cert was co-pro­duced by the Es­planade and SCO and pre­sented as part of the Huayi – Chi­nese Fes­ti­val of Arts 2014.</p>
    <p>www.face­book.com/ sin­ga­pore.chi­nese.orches­tra/videos/</p>


